					<h2>Julie Williamson</h2>
					<h3>Director of Career Services</h3>
					
					<p><img src="images/thumbs/JulieWilliamson.jpg" alt="Laurie" /> After 16 years in the creative arts, Julie Williamson knows how to make connections between people and projects. She facilitates these daily as the Director of Career Services for the Art Institute of Portland. Julie has developed these skills by working in the episodic television, advertising and entertainment production industries, working as a production manager and producer including stints as a freelancer for companies such as Warner Brothers Television and Bond Films, and on staff with such Northwest luminaries as Tyee and Vinton Studios.  Julie also worked as the career advisor for our Animation and Digital Film students and has a true commitment to seeing all our graduates fulfill their ambitions.</p>
					<p>Her passion for serving the creative industries extends beyond the walls of the college as a way of life for Julie. She is currently the President of the Board of Directors of the Oregon Media Production Association, the largest nonprofit film, video and multimedia association in Oregon, a member of the Portland Business Association, and a frequent attendee and participant in creative economy initiatives and industry events in and around Portland.</p>
					<p>Julie&apos;s sense of community participation, personal integrity, gracious humor, program-relevant industry experience, business acumen, and management skills make for a valuable and dynamic leader.  She is dedicated to empowering people to live their dreams and brings that sense of purpose and commitment to every endeavor she undertakes.</p> 
