					<p><img src="images/thumbs/TafflynWilliams.jpg" alt="Tafflyn" /> Three things are becoming increasingly rare in Portland: PC laptops, coffee shops without free wireless and people who were actually born in the city. In Tafflyn Williams-Thomas, the Art Institute managed to find one of the few people who fit into that last category. Born and raised on Portland&apos;s westside, Tafflyn joined our team as a Career Advisor in March 2007.  Before joining us Tafflyn was a workforce development consultant for ten years.  She provided leadership to the Portland Design Festivals and Mayor Katz's Creative Economy Initiative. Her work with post secondary education includes student design showcases, student workshops and a creative services capacity building project.  Tafflyn's placement background includes working with homeless adults, developmentally disabled individuals and youth.  Tafflyn received her Bachelor of Science degree in Rhetoric and Communications at the University of Oregon.</p>
